<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1008,1754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,1088,1114]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[863,1032,1088,1113]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName box="[863,942,1088,1113]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Draconarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutus">acutus</taxonomicName>
, -a -um
</emphasis>
, meaning “sharp” and referring to the sharply pointed distal tip of the conductor; adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1008,1754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,325,1168,1194]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang, Yin, Peng &amp; Xie 1990" authorityName="Wang, Yin, Peng &amp; Xie" authorityYear="1990" box="[632,1274,1168,1194]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Draconarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspinatus">
<emphasis box="[632,902,1168,1193]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">Draconarius aspinatus</emphasis>
(Wang, Yin, Peng &amp; Xie 
<number box="[1206,1266,1168,1194]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" value="1990.0">1990</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having the simple and sharply pointed conductor, but can be easily distinguished by the short cymbial furrow and short median apophysis, the narrow dorsal margin of conductor and the basally originating embolus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
